# UI Quality Standard

Every UI change must move the app toward an AAA-quality game client feel.

## Required qualities
- strong visual hierarchy
- disciplined spacing
- premium surfaces
- clean alignment
- sharp typography
- subtle motion
- clear interaction states
- responsive behavior
- consistent component language

## Avoid
- flat Tailwind blocks
- random gradients
- neon spam
- oversized blur everywhere
- weak spacing
- cheap-looking cards
- inconsistent button styles
- cluttered layouts
- placeholder-feeling sections

## Visual direction
- cinematic
- dark luxury
- arcane archive / codex energy
- collectible-card-first presentation
- restrained glow
- layered glass / metal / stone feel

## Output style
When changing UI:
1. explain the visual problem briefly
2. explain the component strategy briefly
3. implement cleanly
4. keep styles reusable
